# =============================================================================
# Rust / Cargo
# =============================================================================
debug/
target/
# Cargo.lock IS committed for this workspace (binary crates: uffs-cli,
# uffs-daemon, uffs-mcp, etc.).  Committing it is required for:
#   * Reproducible builds (every dev + CI + release resolves the same graph)
#   * Supply-chain integrity (pairs with cargo-vet + cargo-deny pinning)
#   * SLSA attestation integrity (release provenance references a specific
#     dep graph; without Cargo.lock that graph would drift every run)
#   * cargo-vet stability (exemptions are keyed on specific crate-versions
#     — a floating Cargo.lock would break cargo vet check on every
#     unrelated upstream patch release)
# To deliberately update deps, use `cargo update` or a Dependabot PR.
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
# macOS sed -i backup files
*.toml-e
*.yml-e
*.rs-e

# =============================================================================
# Trash / quarantine (local rollback staging)
# =============================================================================
/_trash/*
!/_trash/.gitignore
/_trash/**/.gitkeep
/_trash/**/.keep

# =============================================================================
# Build artifacts & generated binaries
# =============================================================================
# Build artifacts directory — all generated files stay out of git.
build/
*.rlib
*.bin
# `*.bin` is meant to keep transient generated blobs out of git, but the
# workspace contains three INTENTIONAL committed binary assets that must
# remain tracked.  Without these carve-outs, release-plz aborts with
# "the working directory has uncommitted changes" because it sees these
# files as both committed AND gitignored — the same R0-pattern issue
# the `!build/update_all_versions.rs` exception above resolves.  Found
# during R3 release-plz shadow-mode validation; see
# `docs/architecture/release-automation-plan.md` Phase R3.
#
# Upcase tables: `upcase_default.bin` is embedded via `include_bytes!`
# in `crates/uffs-text/src/case_fold.rs` (compile-time dependency).
# `upcase_windows_c.bin` is the Windows-captured reference fixture
# consumed by the `upcase` parity test in `crates/uffs-mft`.
!crates/uffs-text/src/*.bin
# MFT capture fixtures for integration tests; documented in
# `tests/fixtures/README.md`.  Without this carve-out the
# `ipc_integration::real_mft_search` test in `uffs-daemon` cannot find
# its fixture and silently no-ops.
!tests/fixtures/**/*.bin
/test_scf

# =============================================================================
# Logs, vendor, misc
# =============================================================================
/Shell/
# /LOG/ is strictly local-only.  Every file under it — runtime logs
# (defender ETLs, mental_health, `ship_run*.log` captures), per-session
# notes, healing logs, assessment scratchpads, anything — stays on the
# developer's machine and NEVER reaches git.  The project-level
# `CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root is the only changelog that ships.
/LOG/
/vendor/
/missing_paths.txt
/_trash/
/reference/
# Binaries are distributed via GitHub Releases, not committed to the repo
dist/
# Transient pipeline / debug logs captured at the workspace root via `tee`.
# Kept around between healing iterations but never committed.
/.ship_run*.log
/.clippy_run*.log
/.git_status.txt
/.git_show.txt
/.git_lsfiles.txt

# =============================================================================
# IDE / Editor / AI
# =============================================================================
.idea/
.vscode/
.ai/
# Claude Code: local state stays ignored, but the project hook config that
# blocks gate-bypass flags is tracked and shared (scripts/hooks/claude_no_bypass.sh).
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
.qodo/
.reuse/
.windsurf/
*.iws
*.iml

